parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the saddle bag latch can cause the saddle bag lid to open while riding, potentially leading to loss of cargo, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The right saddle bag latch shows signs of excessive wear
the latch is misaligned
the latch is in danger of complete failure
the saddle bag lid may pop open while riding.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the floorboard pins can cause the floorboard to fall off while riding, potentially leading to accidents, injuries, or death.
symptoms: The pins that hold the floorboards in place vibrate forward
the floorboard falls off while riding
the pins need to be adjusted frequently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature shut-off of the turn signal can cause confusion or accidents, especially when slowing down or taking a turn.
symptoms: The turn signal shuts off prematurely
the turn signal shuts off after 15-20 seconds
the turn signal does not function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The dislodging of the C-clip from its groove can cause the transmission gears to travel excessively, leading to a transmission lockup and potentially catastrophic accidents.
symptoms: Transmission lockup
gears traveling more than intended
potential loss of control
and increased risk of accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The abnormal noise from the transmission can be a sign of a more serious underlying issue, potentially leading to transmission failure, loss of vehicle control, and accidents.
symptoms: Unusual noise coming from the transmission
potentially accompanied by vibration or difficulty shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling of the engine and transmission lockup can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: Engine stalling
transmission lockup
loss of power
rear tire lockup
and potential loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling of the bike can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially when merging into traffic, making turns, or starting from a stop.
symptoms: The bike stalls frequently
especially when downshifting or opening the throttle
resulting in a sudden loss of power and affecting the center of gravity and balance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the bike to stall or shut off suddenly, leading to accidents or leaving the rider stranded.
symptoms: The engine shuts off by itself
the lights and electrical components shut off
and the bike is unable to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The erratic or inconsistent turn-signal cancellation can cause confusion and accidents, especially when changing lanes or making turns.
symptoms: The turn signal flashes an inconsistent number of times
sometimes only flashing 5 times
and sometimes flashing 20 times while moving.
